{"questionId":"22583414","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the long-term probability that Urvashi’s van is parked at home.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong><br>attempt to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math> seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>limit of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math> calculated&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><msup><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> must be seen to award <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong><br>attempt to expand their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> using explicit <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Using this method, the limit of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></math> may be inferred and <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em> awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Multiplication by initial condition <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> may be seen at any point as part of their method.</p>\n<p>For an answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> from incomplete methods award a maximum of <strong><em>M1A0A0</em></strong>, or if no working is seen, award <em><strong>M0A0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22583414","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.5f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the long-term probability that Urvashi’s